category.name: fitness
description:
Hej, välkomna till Promenera mera i Stockholm!<br>

Detta är en grupp för er som gillar att gå långpromenader i fantastiskt fina Stockholm året runt! Tanken bakom gruppen är att man ska kunna gå långpromenader med sällskap - för att det är trevligt och kul men också för att det är säkrare (speciellt under vinterhalvåret). Vi går oftast en gång i veckan, både innanför och utanför tullarna, och promenaderna brukar bli runt 8 till 10 km. Vi startar oftast någon gång mellan 18 och 19, och promenaderna tar ungefär 2 timmar. Tanken bakom den sena starttiden är att vi ska kunna hinna mötas upp efter arbetstidens slut, och eventuell hämtning av barn och/eller middag. Alla är välkomna, men det är bra om alla medlemmar orkar gå långa promenader i lagom rask takt. Det är inte powerwalk, men motionstakt. Barn i alla åldrar är välkomna, bara de klarar av att gå längre sträckor. På de flesta turer funkar det att ha barnvagn.

Alla medlemmar får organisera promenader, och alla medlemmar får komma med. Bjud gärna in vänner/bekanta/familj som gillar att promenera – ju fler desto roligare, men större grupp skapar också fler möjligheter att organisera promenader olika dagar i veckan på olika områden i Stockholm.

Promenera mera i Stockholm har gått ett 100-tal promenader sedan start i januari 2015, och många fler är planerade framöver! Vi har en Facebook-sida och en Meetup-grupp dit alla medlemmar är välkomna. Vi har även ett nyhetsbrev som hittills kommit ut två gånger. Förutom långpromenader har vi årligen: en barpromenad runt Södermalm, ca ett par kajakturer på sommaren, några kortare promenader anpassade för barn, och en fitness promenad där vi gör stopp vid utomhusgym. Vi är väldigt öppna för förslag!

Välkommen att promenera mera med oss!

Mail: promenera.mera.stockholm@gmail.com

Hemsida: http://promeneramerastockholm.weebly.com

Ni får gärna höra av er om förändringar eller idéer till våren, antingen här eller på vår mail promenera.mera.stockholm@gmail.com. Vi letar även efter medorganisatörer av varierad engagemangsnivå, så är ni intresserade eller vill veta mer, hör av er! <br>
name: Promenera mera i Stockholm

Det här är ett rop för alla de simmare som gillar att träna / bada långdistans, förbättra uthållighet och teknik! Jag har varit simma lärare i över två år, och en simmare för livet och vill gärna hitta några motiverade, roliga och energiska simkamrater!

Hoppas vi ses snart!

--------------------------------------------------------------------

This is a call out for all those swimmers who who like to train/swim long distance, improve endurance and technique! I've been a swimming teacher for over two years, and a swimmer for a lifetime and would like to find some motivated, fun and energetic swimming companions! 


I swim everyday and my schedule is quite flexible, my preferred schedule is early morning and noon but we can arrange evening if it suits most! I will be swimming in the outside pool at Eriksdalsbadet until its open and the rest of the year I swim in the inside pool.
Hope to see you soon!

parkrun is the world's biggest running movement, with over 4 million registered worldwide, and over 200,000 people running each week at over 1200 events around the world. We also have events in Stockholm in Huddinge and Kungsängen.

category.name: fitness
description:
Hej obstacle racers! This group is for anyone (regardless of fitness level) interested in obstacle races/mud runs like Tough Viking, Toughest, Spartan Race etc., for anyone who enjoys exercising outside or wishes to get in shape to survive the pending zombie apocalypse. Let’s enjoy the great outdoors and put some training in for your upcoming events! I’ve created this group as I very recently moved to Stockholm and as I had a popular club in Edinburgh, I thought I would do the same here as it’s a good way to make friends, find people to become motivated with and do races alongside.

Please also join our new Facebook group:

https://www.facebook.com/groups/StockholmOCR/

Here are some of my credentials; top 10% contender in Worlds Toughest Mudder (24hour Obstacle Race in the Nevada Desert), taken part in ~40+ obstacle races and ex-Muay Thai fighter/coach so we will get you in shape to cross the finish line!

The plan:
Initially, weekly sessions on Saturday mornings at various locations around Stockholm. I will be there rain, hail or snow! #noexcuses We’ll organise an occasional social event too.

If anyone would like to help out in any way, that would be great! I can’t speak Svenska yet, so I’m particularly interested if anyone who can assist with translation etc. Instagram: Movelitefitness

Workouts:
The workouts will last approx. 1-1/4 hour and with an average. 50/50 split between running and exercise drills, although some will be more exercise focused and others more running focused. There will also be crawling (yes, on the grass/mud!), animal inspired movement and partner drills to keep things interesting and I guarantee you, no 2 workouts will be the same. Having done a lot of these races before, I’m very aware that just being able to run long distances is of limited benefit as you need a good level of strength to conquer the obstacles and therefore the workouts will have a high focus on full-body strength building. Post-workout fika may take place sometimes too!

Costs:
Free (we are a non-profit club) but I would kindly ask for an optional 20SEK/session voluntary donation to help cover the Meetup membership fees and most importantly, the rest will go to a ‘to be confirmed’ charity. The club in Edinburgh supported an animal sanctuary and I’d like to do the same here so we just need to decide which one we will support. Feel free to make any suggestions!

Training ethos:
Give it your best and train hard, but in a light-hearted, sociable manner and offer encouragement and support to your training partners. Feel free to invite your friends and importantly, positive vibes only on this group.

Hope to see you all soon for some kickass training! :-D
Carpe diem

This training group is for the road cycling beginner and intermediate rider, who is interested in riding with others and acquiring the basic skills involved therein. The idea is to go for a 45-60 Km ride at a challenging pace, but where everyone can keep up.

Prerequisites are basic bike handling skills and a helmet...

This is not a race, it is exercise. It is important that everyone follows the highway code - færdselsloven - for the safety of themselves, the group and others.

Each ride will start with a little briefing about the route and general group riding tips and tricks.

I am looking forward to going on some great rides in the company of interesting people... so come one, come all!!!

Looking forward to seeing you out there...

 

Please feel free to suggest events for this group!!

category.name: fitness
description:
"A drinking club with a running problem"

We are an international, non-competitive running club. We run every week of the year, on Saturday afternoons in the winter (October to March) and Monday evenings in the summer (April to September). The attendance is usually 30-50 people in the summer, and we get decimated to roughly half of the usual pack by the winter cold.

The start is usually from a parking lot next to a train station or bus stop in the Greater Copenhagen area. Look for a group of people in colourful clothes. Sometimes the way from the station to the meeting point is marked with chalk or flour blobs, especially if there is a parking lot on either way of the rails. When it's cold, bring some warm clothes to put on after the run. There is always at least one car available where you can store your bag during the run. 

Every week we run in a different area, and we don't know the route beforehand - only the so-called hare, i.e. person that marked the trail, knows it, and the rest of us needs to find it by following marks made with flour. Once in a while the trail will stop (it's a so-called "check") and from that point you need to find out where it continues - the marks will continue after 100-200 meters. This way if you're a fast runner, you have a chance to run more by checking out possible trails. If you're a slow runner, there is a chance that the right trail will be found by the time you get to the "check". This way the fastest runner and the slowest walker will most likely finish the run within a few minutes from each other.

We most often run in the forest. If you're a recovering runner or a beginner, you can choose to walk part or all of the trail. The trail is usually roughly 7-10 km, but shortcuts are marked so that walkers and slow runners can end up doing only a 4-6 km trail. Sometimes people ask us what pace we run at. There is no answer to that - everybody runs at the pace that suits them.

After the run we drink beer and sing frivolous songs while praising or punishing fellow members for good or stupid things they did during the run by giving them some more beer to drink.

WE NEVER CANCEL A RUN. We are not scared away by few participants or bad weather. Also, do not get discouraged by few registrations on Meetup. Our club has existed since 1980, and a vast majority of our members check the start location in our calendar (ch3.dk) and just show up. So there is no risk that you will come in vain.

The first run is free. After that the fee is 50 DKK per run, or 222 DKK per quarter. The price includes all beverages during and after the run as well as some snacks (crisps) after the run.

The official language of the Copenhagen Hash House Harriers is English. A lot of us speak Danish though, so if you'd like to practise Danish, there will be plenty of opportunity for that as well.

Read more about us on: www.CH3.dk. 

Read more about the hash house harriers around the world on Wikipedia: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hash_House_Harriers

description:
The Orange Venture Group is dedicated to anyone with interest in keeping fit and outdoor activities with a knack for adventure. Sweden isn't only a great place to live, it offers many fantastic places to explore. We created this group to create a community of people who want to break free from the flatness of everyday life and embark on a weekend trip in the wild, climbing or cycling.

You don't have to be a certified adrenaline junkie to join us, the only thing you need is positive attitude, warm clothes and comfortable hiking shoes.

We meet up every Monday for our signature outdoor training at Bultoftaparken. This is a great opportunity to meet like-minded individuals and get fit. We train mostly for pleasure but weekly training programmes are specifically designed to develop motor skills and target fitness components (strength, power, explosiveness, endurance). OVG is an ideal place to start your training for obstacle racing.

Don't worry about experience, we are happy to accommodate all levels of fitness. Better yet speak to Anna or Olof directly if you have any questions.

Aside from that we often engage in plenty of social events, going out, occasional cookups, friendly badminton or volleyball match, carting etc.

OVG has been created to form a dedicated community of active and adventure-minded people who look to become stronger versions of themselves, maximise their potential and make the most of their spare time while sharing a laugh in the great atmosphere. At the end we're all here to have a great time. Feel free to check it out for yourself. 

PLEASE NOTE: we value the time and commitment of our members above anything else therefore in order to keep it fair between all participants we will be removing members who haven't showed up on meetups without updating their RSPV accordingly no later than an hour before the meetup.

We are looking forward to seeing you at our next training.

Anna and Olof

description:
"A drinking club with a running problem"

We are an international, non-competitive running club. We run every week of the year, on Saturday afternoons in the winter (October to March) and Monday evenings in the summer (April to September). The attendance is usually 30-50 people in the summer, and we get decimated to roughly half of the usual pack by the winter cold.

The start is usually from a parking lot next to a train station or bus stop in the Greater Copenhagen area. Look for a group of people in colourful clothes. Sometimes the way from the station to the meeting point is marked with chalk or flour blobs, especially if there is a parking lot on either way of the rails. When it's cold, bring some warm clothes to put on after the run. There is always at least one car available where you can store your bag during the run. 

Every week we run in a different area, and we don't know the route beforehand - only the so-called hare, i.e. person that marked the trail, knows it, and the rest of us needs to find it by following marks made with flour. Once in a while the trail will stop (it's a so-called "check") and from that point you need to find out where it continues - the marks will continue after 100-200 meters. This way if you're a fast runner, you have a chance to run more by checking out possible trails. If you're a slow runner, there is a chance that the right trail will be found by the time you get to the "check". This way the fastest runner and the slowest walker will most likely finish the run within a few minutes from each other.

We most often run in the forest. If you're a recovering runner or a beginner, you can choose to walk part or all of the trail. The trail is usually roughly 7-10 km, but shortcuts are marked so that walkers and slow runners can end up doing only a 4-6 km trail. Sometimes people ask us what pace we run at. There is no answer to that - everybody runs at the pace that suits them.

After the run we drink beer and sing frivolous songs while praising or punishing fellow members for good or stupid things they did during the run by giving them some more beer to drink.

WE NEVER CANCEL A RUN. We are not scared away by few participants or bad weather. Also, do not get discouraged by few registrations on Meetup. Our club has existed since 1980, and a vast majority of our members check the start location in our calendar (ch3.dk) and just show up. So there is no risk that you will come in vain.

The first run is free. After that the fee is 50 DKK per run, or 222 DKK per quarter. The price includes all beverages during and after the run as well as some snacks (crisps) after the run.

The official language of the Copenhagen Hash House Harriers is English. A lot of us speak Danish though, so if you'd like to practise Danish, there will be plenty of opportunity for that as well.

Read more about us on: www.CH3.dk. 

Read more about the hash house harriers around the world on Wikipedia: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hash_House_Harriers

We love new ideas - if you would like to host a run or workout or would like run at a certain pace and distance let us know and we'll try to set something up!

Chloe & Thor

description:
Pencak Silat er den indonesiske nationalsport. Den kombinerede kampsport og kampkunst fra det indonesiske ø-rige, Pencak Silat Denmark har sit udgangspunkt i Paatje Pfefferkorns (Guru i Holland) stilart Setia Hati Anoman, som opvisnings Pencak med flotte graciøse og til tider akrobatiske bevægelser.

Pencak Silat is the Indonesian national sport. The combined martial arts and martial arts of the Indonesian islands, Pencak Silat Denmark has its origin in Paatje Pfefferkorns (Guru in Holland) style Setia Hati Anoman that choice for performance Pencak with gorgeous graceful and sometimes acrobatic movements.

Vi træner vær lørdag i Gladsaxe hallen, fra klokken 11:00-12:30 <br>Prisen er 50 kr som i bare skal give til martin(instruktør) efter træningen <br>ingen erfaring nødvendig alle er velkommen <br>

We train be Saturday in Gladsaxe hall, from at 11:00-12:30 <br>The price is 50 kr , have it with you and give it to Martin (Instructor) after training. <br>no experience necessary, all are welcome <br>

Hvad skal du huske:

• Tøj du kan lave motion i

• En flaske vand er en god ide

• godt humør :)

What you should remember: <br>

• Clothes you can make exercise in <br>

• A bottle of water is a good idea <br>

• good mood :)

Der er omklædning som vi bare bruger, med mulighed for bad og sauna + hvis i vil i svømmehal efter er der en lige ved siden af, det er dog ikke gratis, men tror ikke det er så dyrt.

There is changing rooms as we just use, with the possibility of bath and sauna + if you want to go swim after, you can do that right next to were we train it's not free, but do not think it is so expensive .

Glæder mig til at se jer, <br>hvis i har nogle spørgsmål må i endelig bare skrive til mig

I look forward to seeing you, <br>If you have any questions just write to me

<br>

<br>

description:
The Orange Venture Group is dedicated to anyone with interest in keeping fit and outdoor activities with a knack for adventure. Sweden isn't only a great place to live, it offers many fantastic places to explore. We created this group to create a community of people who want to break free from the flatness of everyday life and embark on a weekend trip in the wild, climbing or cycling.

You don't have to be a certified adrenaline junkie to join us, the only thing you need is positive attitude, warm clothes and comfortable hiking shoes.

We meet up every Monday for our signature outdoor training at Bultoftaparken. This is a great opportunity to meet like-minded individuals and get fit. We train mostly for pleasure but weekly training programmes are specifically designed to develop motor skills and target fitness components (strength, power, explosiveness, endurance). OVG is an ideal place to start your training for obstacle racing.

Don't worry about experience, we are happy to accommodate all levels of fitness. Better yet speak to Anna or Olof directly if you have any questions.

Aside from that we often engage in plenty of social events, going out, occasional cookups, friendly badminton or volleyball match, carting etc.

OVG has been created to form a dedicated community of active and adventure-minded people who look to become stronger versions of themselves, maximise their potential and make the most of their spare time while sharing a laugh in the great atmosphere. At the end we're all here to have a great time. Feel free to check it out for yourself. 

PLEASE NOTE: we value the time and commitment of our members above anything else therefore in order to keep it fair between all participants we will be removing members who haven't showed up on meetups without updating their RSPV accordingly no later than an hour before the meetup.

We are looking forward to seeing you at our next training.

Anna and Olof

category.name: fitness
description:
Hej, välkomna till Promenera mera i Stockholm!<br>

Detta är en grupp för er som gillar att gå långpromenader i fantastiskt fina Stockholm året runt! Tanken bakom gruppen är att man ska kunna gå långpromenader med sällskap - för att det är trevligt och kul men också för att det är säkrare (speciellt under vinterhalvåret). Vi går oftast en gång i veckan, både innanför och utanför tullarna, och promenaderna brukar bli runt 8 till 10 km. Vi startar oftast någon gång mellan 18 och 19, och promenaderna tar ungefär 2 timmar. Tanken bakom den sena starttiden är att vi ska kunna hinna mötas upp efter arbetstidens slut, och eventuell hämtning av barn och/eller middag. Alla är välkomna, men det är bra om alla medlemmar orkar gå långa promenader i lagom rask takt. Det är inte powerwalk, men motionstakt. Barn i alla åldrar är välkomna, bara de klarar av att gå längre sträckor. På de flesta turer funkar det att ha barnvagn.

Alla medlemmar får organisera promenader, och alla medlemmar får komma med. Bjud gärna in vänner/bekanta/familj som gillar att promenera – ju fler desto roligare, men större grupp skapar också fler möjligheter att organisera promenader olika dagar i veckan på olika områden i Stockholm.

Promenera mera i Stockholm har gått ett 100-tal promenader sedan start i januari 2015, och många fler är planerade framöver! Vi har en Facebook-sida och en Meetup-grupp dit alla medlemmar är välkomna. Vi har även ett nyhetsbrev som hittills kommit ut två gånger. Förutom långpromenader har vi årligen: en barpromenad runt Södermalm, ca ett par kajakturer på sommaren, några kortare promenader anpassade för barn, och en fitness promenad där vi gör stopp vid utomhusgym. Vi är väldigt öppna för förslag!

Välkommen att promenera mera med oss!

Mail: promenera.mera.stockholm@gmail.com

Hemsida: http://promeneramerastockholm.weebly.com

Ni får gärna höra av er om förändringar eller idéer till våren, antingen här eller på vår mail promenera.mera.stockholm@gmail.com. Vi letar även efter medorganisatörer av varierad engagemangsnivå, så är ni intresserade eller vill veta mer, hör av er! <br>

category.name: fitness
description:
Hej obstacle racers! This group is for anyone (regardless of fitness level) interested in obstacle races/mud runs like Tough Viking, Toughest, Spartan Race etc., for anyone who enjoys exercising outside or wishes to get in shape to survive the pending zombie apocalypse. Let’s enjoy the great outdoors and put some training in for your upcoming events! I’ve created this group as I very recently moved to Stockholm and as I had a popular club in Edinburgh, I thought I would do the same here as it’s a good way to make friends, find people to become motivated with and do races alongside.

Please also join our new Facebook group:

https://www.facebook.com/groups/StockholmOCR/

Here are some of my credentials; top 10% contender in Worlds Toughest Mudder (24hour Obstacle Race in the Nevada Desert), taken part in ~40+ obstacle races and ex-Muay Thai fighter/coach so we will get you in shape to cross the finish line!

The plan:
Initially, weekly sessions on Saturday mornings at various locations around Stockholm. I will be there rain, hail or snow! #noexcuses We’ll organise an occasional social event too.

If anyone would like to help out in any way, that would be great! I can’t speak Svenska yet, so I’m particularly interested if anyone who can assist with translation etc. Instagram: Movelitefitness

Workouts:
The workouts will last approx. 1-1/4 hour and with an average. 50/50 split between running and exercise drills, although some will be more exercise focused and others more running focused. There will also be crawling (yes, on the grass/mud!), animal inspired movement and partner drills to keep things interesting and I guarantee you, no 2 workouts will be the same. Having done a lot of these races before, I’m very aware that just being able to run long distances is of limited benefit as you need a good level of strength to conquer the obstacles and therefore the workouts will have a high focus on full-body strength building. Post-workout fika may take place sometimes too!

Costs:
Free (we are a non-profit club) but I would kindly ask for an optional 20SEK/session voluntary donation to help cover the Meetup membership fees and most importantly, the rest will go to a ‘to be confirmed’ charity. The club in Edinburgh supported an animal sanctuary and I’d like to do the same here so we just need to decide which one we will support. Feel free to make any suggestions!

Training ethos:
Give it your best and train hard, but in a light-hearted, sociable manner and offer encouragement and support to your training partners. Feel free to invite your friends and importantly, positive vibes only on this group.

Hope to see you all soon for some kickass training! :-D
Carpe diem
name: Stockholm OCR & Fitness Club - Tough Viking Toughest etc

category.name: fitness
description:
Hej, välkomna till Promenera mera i Stockholm!<br>

Detta är en grupp för er som gillar att gå långpromenader i fantastiskt fina Stockholm året runt! Tanken bakom gruppen är att man ska kunna gå långpromenader med sällskap - för att det är trevligt och kul men också för att det är säkrare (speciellt under vinterhalvåret). Vi går oftast en gång i veckan, både innanför och utanför tullarna, och promenaderna brukar bli runt 8 till 10 km. Vi startar oftast någon gång mellan 18 och 19, och promenaderna tar ungefär 2 timmar. Tanken bakom den sena starttiden är att vi ska kunna hinna mötas upp efter arbetstidens slut, och eventuell hämtning av barn och/eller middag. Alla är välkomna, men det är bra om alla medlemmar orkar gå långa promenader i lagom rask takt. Det är inte powerwalk, men motionstakt. Barn i alla åldrar är välkomna, bara de klarar av att gå längre sträckor. På de flesta turer funkar det att ha barnvagn.

Alla medlemmar får organisera promenader, och alla medlemmar får komma med. Bjud gärna in vänner/bekanta/familj som gillar att promenera – ju fler desto roligare, men större grupp skapar också fler möjligheter att organisera promenader olika dagar i veckan på olika områden i Stockholm.

Promenera mera i Stockholm har gått ett 100-tal promenader sedan start i januari 2015, och många fler är planerade framöver! Vi har en Facebook-sida och en Meetup-grupp dit alla medlemmar är välkomna. Vi har även ett nyhetsbrev som hittills kommit ut två gånger. Förutom långpromenader har vi årligen: en barpromenad runt Södermalm, ca ett par kajakturer på sommaren, några kortare promenader anpassade för barn, och en fitness promenad där vi gör stopp vid utomhusgym. Vi är väldigt öppna för förslag!

Välkommen att promenera mera med oss!

Mail: promenera.mera.stockholm@gmail.com

Hemsida: http://promeneramerastockholm.weebly.com

Ni får gärna höra av er om förändringar eller idéer till våren, antingen här eller på vår mail promenera.mera.stockholm@gmail.com. Vi letar även efter medorganisatörer av varierad engagemangsnivå, så är ni intresserade eller vill veta mer, hör av er! <br>
name: Promenera mera i Stockholm

category.name: fitness
description:
Hej obstacle racers! This group is for anyone (regardless of fitness level) interested in obstacle races/mud runs like Tough Viking, Toughest, Spartan Race etc., for anyone who enjoys exercising outside or wishes to get in shape to survive the pending zombie apocalypse. Let’s enjoy the great outdoors and put some training in for your upcoming events! I’ve created this group as I very recently moved to Stockholm and as I had a popular club in Edinburgh, I thought I would do the same here as it’s a good way to make friends, find people to become motivated with and do races alongside.

Please also join our new Facebook group:

https://www.facebook.com/groups/StockholmOCR/

Here are some of my credentials; top 10% contender in Worlds Toughest Mudder (24hour Obstacle Race in the Nevada Desert), taken part in ~40+ obstacle races and ex-Muay Thai fighter/coach so we will get you in shape to cross the finish line!

The plan:
Initially, weekly sessions on Saturday mornings at various locations around Stockholm. I will be there rain, hail or snow! #noexcuses We’ll organise an occasional social event too.

If anyone would like to help out in any way, that would be great! I can’t speak Svenska yet, so I’m particularly interested if anyone who can assist with translation etc. Instagram: Movelitefitness

Workouts:
The workouts will last approx. 1-1/4 hour and with an average. 50/50 split between running and exercise drills, although some will be more exercise focused and others more running focused. There will also be crawling (yes, on the grass/mud!), animal inspired movement and partner drills to keep things interesting and I guarantee you, no 2 workouts will be the same. Having done a lot of these races before, I’m very aware that just being able to run long distances is of limited benefit as you need a good level of strength to conquer the obstacles and therefore the workouts will have a high focus on full-body strength building. Post-workout fika may take place sometimes too!

Costs:
Free (we are a non-profit club) but I would kindly ask for an optional 20SEK/session voluntary donation to help cover the Meetup membership fees and most importantly, the rest will go to a ‘to be confirmed’ charity. The club in Edinburgh supported an animal sanctuary and I’d like to do the same here so we just need to decide which one we will support. Feel free to make any suggestions!

Training ethos:
Give it your best and train hard, but in a light-hearted, sociable manner and offer encouragement and support to your training partners. Feel free to invite your friends and importantly, positive vibes only on this group.

Hope to see you all soon for some kickass training! :-D
Carpe diem

category.name: fitness
description:
Hej, välkomna till Promenera mera i Stockholm!<br>

Detta är en grupp för er som gillar att gå långpromenader i fantastiskt fina Stockholm året runt! Tanken bakom gruppen är att man ska kunna gå långpromenader med sällskap - för att det är trevligt och kul men också för att det är säkrare (speciellt under vinterhalvåret). Vi går oftast en gång i veckan, både innanför och utanför tullarna, och promenaderna brukar bli runt 8 till 10 km. Vi startar oftast någon gång mellan 18 och 19, och promenaderna tar ungefär 2 timmar. Tanken bakom den sena starttiden är att vi ska kunna hinna mötas upp efter arbetstidens slut, och eventuell hämtning av barn och/eller middag. Alla är välkomna, men det är bra om alla medlemmar orkar gå långa promenader i lagom rask takt. Det är inte powerwalk, men motionstakt. Barn i alla åldrar är välkomna, bara de klarar av att gå längre sträckor. På de flesta turer funkar det att ha barnvagn.

Alla medlemmar får organisera promenader, och alla medlemmar får komma med. Bjud gärna in vänner/bekanta/familj som gillar att promenera – ju fler desto roligare, men större grupp skapar också fler möjligheter att organisera promenader olika dagar i veckan på olika områden i Stockholm.

Promenera mera i Stockholm har gått ett 100-tal promenader sedan start i januari 2015, och många fler är planerade framöver! Vi har en Facebook-sida och en Meetup-grupp dit alla medlemmar är välkomna. Vi har även ett nyhetsbrev som hittills kommit ut två gånger. Förutom långpromenader har vi årligen: en barpromenad runt Södermalm, ca ett par kajakturer på sommaren, några kortare promenader anpassade för barn, och en fitness promenad där vi gör stopp vid utomhusgym. Vi är väldigt öppna för förslag!

Välkommen att promenera mera med oss!

Mail: promenera.mera.stockholm@gmail.com

Hemsida: http://promeneramerastockholm.weebly.com

Ni får gärna höra av er om förändringar eller idéer till våren, antingen här eller på vår mail promenera.mera.stockholm@gmail.com. Vi letar även efter medorganisatörer av varierad engagemangsnivå, så är ni intresserade eller vill veta mer, hör av er! <br>
name: Promenera mera i Stockholm

category.name: fitness
description:
Det här är ett rop för alla de simmare som gillar att träna / bada långdistans, förbättra uthållighet och teknik! Jag har varit simma lärare i över två år, och en simmare för livet och vill gärna hitta några motiverade, roliga och energiska simkamrater!

Jag simmar varje dag och mitt schema är ganska flexibelt, mitt föredragna schema är tidigt på morgonen och middag men vi kan ordna kvällen om det passar mest! Jag kommer att simma i poolen vid Eriksdalsbadet tills den är öppen och resten av året svimmar jag i insidan poolen.

Hoppas vi ses snart!

--------------------------------------------------------------------

This is a call out for all those swimmers who who like to train/swim long distance, improve endurance and technique! I've been a swimming teacher for over two years, and a swimmer for a lifetime and would like to find some motivated, fun and energetic swimming companions! 


I swim everyday and my schedule is quite flexible, my preferred schedule is early morning and noon but we can arrange evening if it suits most! I will be swimming in the outside pool at Eriksdalsbadet until its open and the rest of the year I swim in the inside pool.
Hope to see you soon!
name: Stockholm Long Swimming

category.name: fitness
description:
Everyone is welcome to come and join us at Haga parkrun! Haga parkrun is a 5km timed run that takes place in Hagaparken every Saturday morning at 9.30, all year round. The meeting place is just north of the tennis courts at the southern end of the park, near Haga Forum. It's simple - sign up once at www.parkrun.se/register, print out your barcode and then just bring it along with you when you come to run! You can find all information about Haga parkrun at www.parkrun.se/haga or our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/hagaparkrun/ (where you can also see if ever we have to cancel the event)

parkrun is the world's biggest running movement, with over 4 million registered worldwide, and over 200,000 people running each week at over 1200 events around the world. We also have events in Stockholm in Huddinge and Kungsängen.
name: Haga parkrun

description:
Det här är ett rop för alla de simmare som gillar att träna / bada långdistans, förbättra uthållighet och teknik! Jag har varit simma lärare i över två år, och en simmare för livet och vill gärna hitta några motiverade, roliga och energiska simkamrater!

Jag simmar varje dag och mitt schema är ganska flexibelt, mitt föredragna schema är tidigt på morgonen och middag men vi kan ordna kvällen om det passar mest! Jag kommer att simma i poolen vid Eriksdalsbadet tills den är öppen och resten av året svimmar jag i insidan poolen.

Hoppas vi ses snart!

--------------------------------------------------------------------

This is a call out for all those swimmers who who like to train/swim long distance, improve endurance and technique! I've been a swimming teacher for over two years, and a swimmer for a lifetime and would like to find some motivated, fun and energetic swimming companions! 


I swim everyday and my schedule is quite flexible, my preferred schedule is early morning and noon but we can arrange evening if it suits most! I will be swimming in the outside pool at Eriksdalsbadet until its open and the rest of the year I swim in the inside pool.
Hope to see you soon!

Everyone is welcome to come and join us at Haga parkrun! Haga parkrun is a 5km timed run that takes place in Hagaparken every Saturday morning at 9.30, all year round. The meeting place is just north of the tennis courts at the southern end of the park, near Haga Forum. It's simple - sign up once at www.parkrun.se/register, print out your barcode and then just bring it along with you when you come to run! You can find all information about Haga parkrun at www.parkrun.se/haga or our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/hagaparkrun/ (where you can also see if ever we have to cancel the event)

parkrun is the world's biggest running movement, with over 4 million registered worldwide, and over 200,000 people running each week at over 1200 events around the world. We also have events in Stockholm in Huddinge and Kungsängen.

category.name: fitness
description:
Hej obstacle racers! This group is for anyone (regardless of fitness level) interested in obstacle races/mud runs like Tough Viking, Toughest, Spartan Race etc., for anyone who enjoys exercising outside or wishes to get in shape to survive the pending zombie apocalypse. Let’s enjoy the great outdoors and put some training in for your upcoming events! I’ve created this group as I very recently moved to Stockholm and as I had a popular club in Edinburgh, I thought I would do the same here as it’s a good way to make friends, find people to become motivated with and do races alongside.

Please also join our new Facebook group:

https://www.facebook.com/groups/StockholmOCR/

Here are some of my credentials; top 10% contender in Worlds Toughest Mudder (24hour Obstacle Race in the Nevada Desert), taken part in ~40+ obstacle races and ex-Muay Thai fighter/coach so we will get you in shape to cross the finish line!

The plan:
Initially, weekly sessions on Saturday mornings at various locations around Stockholm. I will be there rain, hail or snow! #noexcuses We’ll organise an occasional social event too.

If anyone would like to help out in any way, that would be great! I can’t speak Svenska yet, so I’m particularly interested if anyone who can assist with translation etc. Instagram: Movelitefitness

Workouts:
The workouts will last approx. 1-1/4 hour and with an average. 50/50 split between running and exercise drills, although some will be more exercise focused and others more running focused. There will also be crawling (yes, on the grass/mud!), animal inspired movement and partner drills to keep things interesting and I guarantee you, no 2 workouts will be the same. Having done a lot of these races before, I’m very aware that just being able to run long distances is of limited benefit as you need a good level of strength to conquer the obstacles and therefore the workouts will have a high focus on full-body strength building. Post-workout fika may take place sometimes too!

Costs:
Free (we are a non-profit club) but I would kindly ask for an optional 20SEK/session voluntary donation to help cover the Meetup membership fees and most importantly, the rest will go to a ‘to be confirmed’ charity. The club in Edinburgh supported an animal sanctuary and I’d like to do the same here so we just need to decide which one we will support. Feel free to make any suggestions!

Training ethos:
Give it your best and train hard, but in a light-hearted, sociable manner and offer encouragement and support to your training partners. Feel free to invite your friends and importantly, positive vibes only on this group.

Hope to see you all soon for some kickass training! :-D
Carpe diem
name: Stockholm OCR & Fitness Club - Tough Viking Toughest etc

description:
This training group is for the road cycling beginner and intermediate rider, who is interested in riding with others and acquiring the basic skills involved therein. The idea is to go for a 45-60 Km ride at a challenging pace, but where everyone can keep up.

Prerequisites are basic bike handling skills and a helmet...

This is not a race, it is exercise. It is important that everyone follows the highway code - færdselsloven - for the safety of themselves, the group and others.

Each ride will start with a little briefing about the route and general group riding tips and tricks.

I am looking forward to going on some great rides in the company of interesting people... so come one, come all!!!

Looking forward to seeing you out there...

 

Please feel free to suggest events for this group!!

category.name: fitness
description:
"A drinking club with a running problem"

We are an international, non-competitive running club. We run every week of the year, on Saturday afternoons in the winter (October to March) and Monday evenings in the summer (April to September). The attendance is usually 30-50 people in the summer, and we get decimated to roughly half of the usual pack by the winter cold.

The start is usually from a parking lot next to a train station or bus stop in the Greater Copenhagen area. Look for a group of people in colourful clothes. Sometimes the way from the station to the meeting point is marked with chalk or flour blobs, especially if there is a parking lot on either way of the rails. When it's cold, bring some warm clothes to put on after the run. There is always at least one car available where you can store your bag during the run. 

Every week we run in a different area, and we don't know the route beforehand - only the so-called hare, i.e. person that marked the trail, knows it, and the rest of us needs to find it by following marks made with flour. Once in a while the trail will stop (it's a so-called "check") and from that point you need to find out where it continues - the marks will continue after 100-200 meters. This way if you're a fast runner, you have a chance to run more by checking out possible trails. If you're a slow runner, there is a chance that the right trail will be found by the time you get to the "check". This way the fastest runner and the slowest walker will most likely finish the run within a few minutes from each other.

We most often run in the forest. If you're a recovering runner or a beginner, you can choose to walk part or all of the trail. The trail is usually roughly 7-10 km, but shortcuts are marked so that walkers and slow runners can end up doing only a 4-6 km trail. Sometimes people ask us what pace we run at. There is no answer to that - everybody runs at the pace that suits them.

After the run we drink beer and sing frivolous songs while praising or punishing fellow members for good or stupid things they did during the run by giving them some more beer to drink.

WE NEVER CANCEL A RUN. We are not scared away by few participants or bad weather. Also, do not get discouraged by few registrations on Meetup. Our club has existed since 1980, and a vast majority of our members check the start location in our calendar (ch3.dk) and just show up. So there is no risk that you will come in vain.

The first run is free. After that the fee is 50 DKK per run, or 222 DKK per quarter. The price includes all beverages during and after the run as well as some snacks (crisps) after the run.

The official language of the Copenhagen Hash House Harriers is English. A lot of us speak Danish though, so if you'd like to practise Danish, there will be plenty of opportunity for that as well.

Read more about us on: www.CH3.dk. 

Read more about the hash house harriers around the world on Wikipedia: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hash_House_Harriers
name: Copenhagen Hash House Harriers (fun, social running)

description:
Pencak Silat er den indonesiske nationalsport. Den kombinerede kampsport og kampkunst fra det indonesiske ø-rige, Pencak Silat Denmark har sit udgangspunkt i Paatje Pfefferkorns (Guru i Holland) stilart Setia Hati Anoman, som opvisnings Pencak med flotte graciøse og til tider akrobatiske bevægelser.

Pencak Silat is the Indonesian national sport. The combined martial arts and martial arts of the Indonesian islands, Pencak Silat Denmark has its origin in Paatje Pfefferkorns (Guru in Holland) style Setia Hati Anoman that choice for performance Pencak with gorgeous graceful and sometimes acrobatic movements.

Vi træner vær lørdag i Gladsaxe hallen, fra klokken 11:00-12:30 <br>Prisen er 50 kr som i bare skal give til martin(instruktør) efter træningen <br>ingen erfaring nødvendig alle er velkommen <br>

We train be Saturday in Gladsaxe hall, from at 11:00-12:30 <br>The price is 50 kr , have it with you and give it to Martin (Instructor) after training. <br>no experience necessary, all are welcome <br>

Hvad skal du huske:

• Tøj du kan lave motion i

• En flaske vand er en god ide

• godt humør :)

What you should remember: <br>

• Clothes you can make exercise in <br>

• A bottle of water is a good idea <br>

• good mood :)

Der er omklædning som vi bare bruger, med mulighed for bad og sauna + hvis i vil i svømmehal efter er der en lige ved siden af, det er dog ikke gratis, men tror ikke det er så dyrt.

There is changing rooms as we just use, with the possibility of bath and sauna + if you want to go swim after, you can do that right next to were we train it's not free, but do not think it is so expensive .

Glæder mig til at se jer, <br>hvis i har nogle spørgsmål må i endelig bare skrive til mig

I look forward to seeing you, <br>If you have any questions just write to me

<br>

<br>

category.name: fitness
description:
The Orange Venture Group is dedicated to anyone with interest in keeping fit and outdoor activities with a knack for adventure. Sweden isn't only a great place to live, it offers many fantastic places to explore. We created this group to create a community of people who want to break free from the flatness of everyday life and embark on a weekend trip in the wild, climbing or cycling.

You don't have to be a certified adrenaline junkie to join us, the only thing you need is positive attitude, warm clothes and comfortable hiking shoes.

We meet up every Monday for our signature outdoor training at Bultoftaparken. This is a great opportunity to meet like-minded individuals and get fit. We train mostly for pleasure but weekly training programmes are specifically designed to develop motor skills and target fitness components (strength, power, explosiveness, endurance). OVG is an ideal place to start your training for obstacle racing.

Don't worry about experience, we are happy to accommodate all levels of fitness. Better yet speak to Anna or Olof directly if you have any questions.

Aside from that we often engage in plenty of social events, going out, occasional cookups, friendly badminton or volleyball match, carting etc.

OVG has been created to form a dedicated community of active and adventure-minded people who look to become stronger versions of themselves, maximise their potential and make the most of their spare time while sharing a laugh in the great atmosphere. At the end we're all here to have a great time. Feel free to check it out for yourself. 

PLEASE NOTE: we value the time and commitment of our members above anything else therefore in order to keep it fair between all participants we will be removing members who haven't showed up on meetups without updating their RSPV accordingly no later than an hour before the meetup.

We are looking forward to seeing you at our next training.

Anna and Olof

category.name: fitness
description:
Hej, välkomna till Promenera mera i Stockholm!<br>

Detta är en grupp för er som gillar att gå långpromenader i fantastiskt fina Stockholm året runt! Tanken bakom gruppen är att man ska kunna gå långpromenader med sällskap - för att det är trevligt och kul men också för att det är säkrare (speciellt under vinterhalvåret). Vi går oftast en gång i veckan, både innanför och utanför tullarna, och promenaderna brukar bli runt 8 till 10 km. Vi startar oftast någon gång mellan 18 och 19, och promenaderna tar ungefär 2 timmar. Tanken bakom den sena starttiden är att vi ska kunna hinna mötas upp efter arbetstidens slut, och eventuell hämtning av barn och/eller middag. Alla är välkomna, men det är bra om alla medlemmar orkar gå långa promenader i lagom rask takt. Det är inte powerwalk, men motionstakt. Barn i alla åldrar är välkomna, bara de klarar av att gå längre sträckor. På de flesta turer funkar det att ha barnvagn.

Alla medlemmar får organisera promenader, och alla medlemmar får komma med. Bjud gärna in vänner/bekanta/familj som gillar att promenera – ju fler desto roligare, men större grupp skapar också fler möjligheter att organisera promenader olika dagar i veckan på olika områden i Stockholm.

Promenera mera i Stockholm har gått ett 100-tal promenader sedan start i januari 2015, och många fler är planerade framöver! Vi har en Facebook-sida och en Meetup-grupp dit alla medlemmar är välkomna. Vi har även ett nyhetsbrev som hittills kommit ut två gånger. Förutom långpromenader har vi årligen: en barpromenad runt Södermalm, ca ett par kajakturer på sommaren, några kortare promenader anpassade för barn, och en fitness promenad där vi gör stopp vid utomhusgym. Vi är väldigt öppna för förslag!

Välkommen att promenera mera med oss!

Mail: promenera.mera.stockholm@gmail.com

Hemsida: http://promeneramerastockholm.weebly.com

Ni får gärna höra av er om förändringar eller idéer till våren, antingen här eller på vår mail promenera.mera.stockholm@gmail.com. Vi letar även efter medorganisatörer av varierad engagemangsnivå, så är ni intresserade eller vill veta mer, hör av er! <br>
name: Promenera mera i Stockholm

description:
Det här är ett rop för alla de simmare som gillar att träna / bada långdistans, förbättra uthållighet och teknik! Jag har varit simma lärare i över två år, och en simmare för livet och vill gärna hitta några motiverade, roliga och energiska simkamrater!

Jag simmar varje dag och mitt schema är ganska flexibelt, mitt föredragna schema är tidigt på morgonen och middag men vi kan ordna kvällen om det passar mest! Jag kommer att simma i poolen vid Eriksdalsbadet tills den är öppen och resten av året svimmar jag i insidan poolen.

Hoppas vi ses snart!

--------------------------------------------------------------------

This is a call out for all those swimmers who who like to train/swim long distance, improve endurance and technique! I've been a swimming teacher for over two years, and a swimmer for a lifetime and would like to find some motivated, fun and energetic swimming companions! 


I swim everyday and my schedule is quite flexible, my preferred schedule is early morning and noon but we can arrange evening if it suits most! I will be swimming in the outside pool at Eriksdalsbadet until its open and the rest of the year I swim in the inside pool.
Hope to see you soon!

Everyone is welcome to come and join us at Haga parkrun! Haga parkrun is a 5km timed run that takes place in Hagaparken every Saturday morning at 9.30, all year round. The meeting place is just north of the tennis courts at the southern end of the park, near Haga Forum. It's simple - sign up once at www.parkrun.se/register, print out your barcode and then just bring it along with you when you come to run! You can find all information about Haga parkrun at www.parkrun.se/haga or our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/hagaparkrun/ (where you can also see if ever we have to cancel the event)

parkrun is the world's biggest running movement, with over 4 million registered worldwide, and over 200,000 people running each week at over 1200 events around the world. We also have events in Stockholm in Huddinge and Kungsängen.

category.name: fitness
description:
Hej obstacle racers! This group is for anyone (regardless of fitness level) interested in obstacle races/mud runs like Tough Viking, Toughest, Spartan Race etc., for anyone who enjoys exercising outside or wishes to get in shape to survive the pending zombie apocalypse. Let’s enjoy the great outdoors and put some training in for your upcoming events! I’ve created this group as I very recently moved to Stockholm and as I had a popular club in Edinburgh, I thought I would do the same here as it’s a good way to make friends, find people to become motivated with and do races alongside.

Please also join our new Facebook group:

https://www.facebook.com/groups/StockholmOCR/

Here are some of my credentials; top 10% contender in Worlds Toughest Mudder (24hour Obstacle Race in the Nevada Desert), taken part in ~40+ obstacle races and ex-Muay Thai fighter/coach so we will get you in shape to cross the finish line!

The plan:
Initially, weekly sessions on Saturday mornings at various locations around Stockholm. I will be there rain, hail or snow! #noexcuses We’ll organise an occasional social event too.

If anyone would like to help out in any way, that would be great! I can’t speak Svenska yet, so I’m particularly interested if anyone who can assist with translation etc. Instagram: Movelitefitness

Workouts:
The workouts will last approx. 1-1/4 hour and with an average. 50/50 split between running and exercise drills, although some will be more exercise focused and others more running focused. There will also be crawling (yes, on the grass/mud!), animal inspired movement and partner drills to keep things interesting and I guarantee you, no 2 workouts will be the same. Having done a lot of these races before, I’m very aware that just being able to run long distances is of limited benefit as you need a good level of strength to conquer the obstacles and therefore the workouts will have a high focus on full-body strength building. Post-workout fika may take place sometimes too!

Costs:
Free (we are a non-profit club) but I would kindly ask for an optional 20SEK/session voluntary donation to help cover the Meetup membership fees and most importantly, the rest will go to a ‘to be confirmed’ charity. The club in Edinburgh supported an animal sanctuary and I’d like to do the same here so we just need to decide which one we will support. Feel free to make any suggestions!

Training ethos:
Give it your best and train hard, but in a light-hearted, sociable manner and offer encouragement and support to your training partners. Feel free to invite your friends and importantly, positive vibes only on this group.

Hope to see you all soon for some kickass training! :-D
Carpe diem
name: Stockholm OCR & Fitness Club - Tough Viking Toughest etc

description:
This training group is for the road cycling beginner and intermediate rider, who is interested in riding with others and acquiring the basic skills involved therein. The idea is to go for a 45-60 Km ride at a challenging pace, but where everyone can keep up.

Prerequisites are basic bike handling skills and a helmet...

This is not a race, it is exercise. It is important that everyone follows the highway code - færdselsloven - for the safety of themselves, the group and others.

Each ride will start with a little briefing about the route and general group riding tips and tricks.

I am looking forward to going on some great rides in the company of interesting people... so come one, come all!!!

Looking forward to seeing you out there...

 

Please feel free to suggest events for this group!!

category.name: fitness
description:
"A drinking club with a running problem"

We are an international, non-competitive running club. We run every week of the year, on Saturday afternoons in the winter (October to March) and Monday evenings in the summer (April to September). The attendance is usually 30-50 people in the summer, and we get decimated to roughly half of the usual pack by the winter cold.

The start is usually from a parking lot next to a train station or bus stop in the Greater Copenhagen area. Look for a group of people in colourful clothes. Sometimes the way from the station to the meeting point is marked with chalk or flour blobs, especially if there is a parking lot on either way of the rails. When it's cold, bring some warm clothes to put on after the run. There is always at least one car available where you can store your bag during the run. 

Every week we run in a different area, and we don't know the route beforehand - only the so-called hare, i.e. person that marked the trail, knows it, and the rest of us needs to find it by following marks made with flour. Once in a while the trail will stop (it's a so-called "check") and from that point you need to find out where it continues - the marks will continue after 100-200 meters. This way if you're a fast runner, you have a chance to run more by checking out possible trails. If you're a slow runner, there is a chance that the right trail will be found by the time you get to the "check". This way the fastest runner and the slowest walker will most likely finish the run within a few minutes from each other.

We most often run in the forest. If you're a recovering runner or a beginner, you can choose to walk part or all of the trail. The trail is usually roughly 7-10 km, but shortcuts are marked so that walkers and slow runners can end up doing only a 4-6 km trail. Sometimes people ask us what pace we run at. There is no answer to that - everybody runs at the pace that suits them.

After the run we drink beer and sing frivolous songs while praising or punishing fellow members for good or stupid things they did during the run by giving them some more beer to drink.

WE NEVER CANCEL A RUN. We are not scared away by few participants or bad weather. Also, do not get discouraged by few registrations on Meetup. Our club has existed since 1980, and a vast majority of our members check the start location in our calendar (ch3.dk) and just show up. So there is no risk that you will come in vain.

The first run is free. After that the fee is 50 DKK per run, or 222 DKK per quarter. The price includes all beverages during and after the run as well as some snacks (crisps) after the run.

The official language of the Copenhagen Hash House Harriers is English. A lot of us speak Danish though, so if you'd like to practise Danish, there will be plenty of opportunity for that as well.

Read more about us on: www.CH3.dk. 

Read more about the hash house harriers around the world on Wikipedia: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hash_House_Harriers
name: Copenhagen Hash House Harriers (fun, social running)

Pencak Silat er den indonesiske nationalsport. Den kombinerede kampsport og kampkunst fra det indonesiske ø-rige, Pencak Silat Denmark har sit udgangspunkt i Paatje Pfefferkorns (Guru i Holland) stilart Setia Hati Anoman, som opvisnings Pencak med flotte graciøse og til tider akrobatiske bevægelser.

Pencak Silat is the Indonesian national sport. The combined martial arts and martial arts of the Indonesian islands, Pencak Silat Denmark has its origin in Paatje Pfefferkorns (Guru in Holland) style Setia Hati Anoman that choice for performance Pencak with gorgeous graceful and sometimes acrobatic movements.

Vi træner vær lørdag i Gladsaxe hallen, fra klokken 11:00-12:30 <br>Prisen er 50 kr som i bare skal give til martin(instruktør) efter træningen <br>ingen erfaring nødvendig alle er velkommen <br>

We train be Saturday in Gladsaxe hall, from at 11:00-12:30 <br>The price is 50 kr , have it with you and give it to Martin (Instructor) after training. <br>no experience necessary, all are welcome <br>

Hvad skal du huske:

• Tøj du kan lave motion i

• En flaske vand er en god ide

• godt humør :)

What you should remember: <br>

• Clothes you can make exercise in <br>

• A bottle of water is a good idea <br>

• good mood :)

Der er omklædning som vi bare bruger, med mulighed for bad og sauna + hvis i vil i svømmehal efter er der en lige ved siden af, det er dog ikke gratis, men tror ikke det er så dyrt.

There is changing rooms as we just use, with the possibility of bath and sauna + if you want to go swim after, you can do that right next to were we train it's not free, but do not think it is so expensive .

Glæder mig til at se jer, <br>hvis i har nogle spørgsmål må i endelig bare skrive til mig

I look forward to seeing you, <br>If you have any questions just write to me

<br>

category.name: fitness
description:
The Orange Venture Group is dedicated to anyone with interest in keeping fit and outdoor activities with a knack for adventure. Sweden isn't only a great place to live, it offers many fantastic places to explore. We created this group to create a community of people who want to break free from the flatness of everyday life and embark on a weekend trip in the wild, climbing or cycling.

You don't have to be a certified adrenaline junkie to join us, the only thing you need is positive attitude, warm clothes and comfortable hiking shoes.

We meet up every Monday for our signature outdoor training at Bultoftaparken. This is a great opportunity to meet like-minded individuals and get fit. We train mostly for pleasure but weekly training programmes are specifically designed to develop motor skills and target fitness components (strength, power, explosiveness, endurance). OVG is an ideal place to start your training for obstacle racing.

Don't worry about experience, we are happy to accommodate all levels of fitness. Better yet speak to Anna or Olof directly if you have any questions.

Aside from that we often engage in plenty of social events, going out, occasional cookups, friendly badminton or volleyball match, carting etc.

OVG has been created to form a dedicated community of active and adventure-minded people who look to become stronger versions of themselves, maximise their potential and make the most of their spare time while sharing a laugh in the great atmosphere. At the end we're all here to have a great time. Feel free to check it out for yourself. 

PLEASE NOTE: we value the time and commitment of our members above anything else therefore in order to keep it fair between all participants we will be removing members who haven't showed up on meetups without updating their RSPV accordingly no later than an hour before the meetup.

We are looking forward to seeing you at our next training.

Anna and Olof
name: The Orange Venture Group - Malmö

category.name: fitness
description:
Hej, välkomna till Promenera mera i Stockholm!<br>

Detta är en grupp för er som gillar att gå långpromenader i fantastiskt fina Stockholm året runt! Tanken bakom gruppen är att man ska kunna gå långpromenader med sällskap - för att det är trevligt och kul men också för att det är säkrare (speciellt under vinterhalvåret). Vi går oftast en gång i veckan, både innanför och utanför tullarna, och promenaderna brukar bli runt 8 till 10 km. Vi startar oftast någon gång mellan 18 och 19, och promenaderna tar ungefär 2 timmar. Tanken bakom den sena starttiden är att vi ska kunna hinna mötas upp efter arbetstidens slut, och eventuell hämtning av barn och/eller middag. Alla är välkomna, men det är bra om alla medlemmar orkar gå långa promenader i lagom rask takt. Det är inte powerwalk, men motionstakt. Barn i alla åldrar är välkomna, bara de klarar av att gå längre sträckor. På de flesta turer funkar det att ha barnvagn.

Alla medlemmar får organisera promenader, och alla medlemmar får komma med. Bjud gärna in vänner/bekanta/familj som gillar att promenera – ju fler desto roligare, men större grupp skapar också fler möjligheter att organisera promenader olika dagar i veckan på olika områden i Stockholm.

Promenera mera i Stockholm har gått ett 100-tal promenader sedan start i januari 2015, och många fler är planerade framöver! Vi har en Facebook-sida och en Meetup-grupp dit alla medlemmar är välkomna. Vi har även ett nyhetsbrev som hittills kommit ut två gånger. Förutom långpromenader har vi årligen: en barpromenad runt Södermalm, ca ett par kajakturer på sommaren, några kortare promenader anpassade för barn, och en fitness promenad där vi gör stopp vid utomhusgym. Vi är väldigt öppna för förslag!

Välkommen att promenera mera med oss!

Mail: promenera.mera.stockholm@gmail.com

Hemsida: http://promeneramerastockholm.weebly.com

Ni får gärna höra av er om förändringar eller idéer till våren, antingen här eller på vår mail promenera.mera.stockholm@gmail.com. Vi letar även efter medorganisatörer av varierad engagemangsnivå, så är ni intresserade eller vill veta mer, hör av er! <br>
name: Promenera mera i Stockholm

category.name: fitness
description:
Hej obstacle racers! This group is for anyone (regardless of fitness level) interested in obstacle races/mud runs like Tough Viking, Toughest, Spartan Race etc., for anyone who enjoys exercising outside or wishes to get in shape to survive the pending zombie apocalypse. Let’s enjoy the great outdoors and put some training in for your upcoming events! I’ve created this group as I very recently moved to Stockholm and as I had a popular club in Edinburgh, I thought I would do the same here as it’s a good way to make friends, find people to become motivated with and do races alongside.

Please also join our new Facebook group:

https://www.facebook.com/groups/StockholmOCR/

Here are some of my credentials; top 10% contender in Worlds Toughest Mudder (24hour Obstacle Race in the Nevada Desert), taken part in ~40+ obstacle races and ex-Muay Thai fighter/coach so we will get you in shape to cross the finish line!

The plan:
Initially, weekly sessions on Saturday mornings at various locations around Stockholm. I will be there rain, hail or snow! #noexcuses We’ll organise an occasional social event too.

If anyone would like to help out in any way, that would be great! I can’t speak Svenska yet, so I’m particularly interested if anyone who can assist with translation etc. Instagram: Movelitefitness

Workouts:
The workouts will last approx. 1-1/4 hour and with an average. 50/50 split between running and exercise drills, although some will be more exercise focused and others more running focused. There will also be crawling (yes, on the grass/mud!), animal inspired movement and partner drills to keep things interesting and I guarantee you, no 2 workouts will be the same. Having done a lot of these races before, I’m very aware that just being able to run long distances is of limited benefit as you need a good level of strength to conquer the obstacles and therefore the workouts will have a high focus on full-body strength building. Post-workout fika may take place sometimes too!

Costs:
Free (we are a non-profit club) but I would kindly ask for an optional 20SEK/session voluntary donation to help cover the Meetup membership fees and most importantly, the rest will go to a ‘to be confirmed’ charity. The club in Edinburgh supported an animal sanctuary and I’d like to do the same here so we just need to decide which one we will support. Feel free to make any suggestions!

Training ethos:
Give it your best and train hard, but in a light-hearted, sociable manner and offer encouragement and support to your training partners. Feel free to invite your friends and importantly, positive vibes only on this group.

Hope to see you all soon for some kickass training! :-D
Carpe diem

category.name: fitness
description:
Hej, välkomna till Promenera mera i Stockholm!<br>

Detta är en grupp för er som gillar att gå långpromenader i fantastiskt fina Stockholm året runt! Tanken bakom gruppen är att man ska kunna gå långpromenader med sällskap - för att det är trevligt och kul men också för att det är säkrare (speciellt under vinterhalvåret). Vi går oftast en gång i veckan, både innanför och utanför tullarna, och promenaderna brukar bli runt 8 till 10 km. Vi startar oftast någon gång mellan 18 och 19, och promenaderna tar ungefär 2 timmar. Tanken bakom den sena starttiden är att vi ska kunna hinna mötas upp efter arbetstidens slut, och eventuell hämtning av barn och/eller middag. Alla är välkomna, men det är bra om alla medlemmar orkar gå långa promenader i lagom rask takt. Det är inte powerwalk, men motionstakt. Barn i alla åldrar är välkomna, bara de klarar av att gå längre sträckor. På de flesta turer funkar det att ha barnvagn.

Alla medlemmar får organisera promenader, och alla medlemmar får komma med. Bjud gärna in vänner/bekanta/familj som gillar att promenera – ju fler desto roligare, men större grupp skapar också fler möjligheter att organisera promenader olika dagar i veckan på olika områden i Stockholm.

Promenera mera i Stockholm har gått ett 100-tal promenader sedan start i januari 2015, och många fler är planerade framöver! Vi har en Facebook-sida och en Meetup-grupp dit alla medlemmar är välkomna. Vi har även ett nyhetsbrev som hittills kommit ut två gånger. Förutom långpromenader har vi årligen: en barpromenad runt Södermalm, ca ett par kajakturer på sommaren, några kortare promenader anpassade för barn, och en fitness promenad där vi gör stopp vid utomhusgym. Vi är väldigt öppna för förslag!

Välkommen att promenera mera med oss!

Mail: promenera.mera.stockholm@gmail.com

Hemsida: http://promeneramerastockholm.weebly.com

Ni får gärna höra av er om förändringar eller idéer till våren, antingen här eller på vår mail promenera.mera.stockholm@gmail.com. Vi letar även efter medorganisatörer av varierad engagemangsnivå, så är ni intresserade eller vill veta mer, hör av er! <br>
name: Promenera mera i Stockholm
organizer.name: Linda

description:
Det här är ett rop för alla de simmare som gillar att träna / bada långdistans, förbättra uthållighet och teknik! Jag har varit simma lärare i över två år, och en simmare för livet och vill gärna hitta några motiverade, roliga och energiska simkamrater!

Jag simmar varje dag och mitt schema är ganska flexibelt, mitt föredragna schema är tidigt på morgonen och middag men vi kan ordna kvällen om det passar mest! Jag kommer att simma i poolen vid Eriksdalsbadet tills den är öppen och resten av året svimmar jag i insidan poolen.

Hoppas vi ses snart!

--------------------------------------------------------------------

This is a call out for all those swimmers who who like to train/swim long distance, improve endurance and technique! I've been a swimming teacher for over two years, and a swimmer for a lifetime and would like to find some motivated, fun and energetic swimming companions! 


I swim everyday and my schedule is quite flexible, my preferred schedule is early morning and noon but we can arrange evening if it suits most! I will be swimming in the outside pool at Eriksdalsbadet until its open and the rest of the year I swim in the inside pool.
Hope to see you soon!
name: Stockholm Long Swimming

description:
Everyone is welcome to come and join us at Haga parkrun! Haga parkrun is a 5km timed run that takes place in Hagaparken every Saturday morning at 9.30, all year round. The meeting place is just north of the tennis courts at the southern end of the park, near Haga Forum. It's simple - sign up once at www.parkrun.se/register, print out your barcode and then just bring it along with you when you come to run! You can find all information about Haga parkrun at www.parkrun.se/haga or our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/hagaparkrun/ (where you can also see if ever we have to cancel the event)

parkrun is the world's biggest running movement, with over 4 million registered worldwide, and over 200,000 people running each week at over 1200 events around the world. We also have events in Stockholm in Huddinge and Kungsängen.
name: Haga parkrun

category.name: fitness
description:
Hej obstacle racers! This group is for anyone (regardless of fitness level) interested in obstacle races/mud runs like Tough Viking, Toughest, Spartan Race etc., for anyone who enjoys exercising outside or wishes to get in shape to survive the pending zombie apocalypse. Let’s enjoy the great outdoors and put some training in for your upcoming events! I’ve created this group as I very recently moved to Stockholm and as I had a popular club in Edinburgh, I thought I would do the same here as it’s a good way to make friends, find people to become motivated with and do races alongside.

Please also join our new Facebook group:

https://www.facebook.com/groups/StockholmOCR/

Here are some of my credentials; top 10% contender in Worlds Toughest Mudder (24hour Obstacle Race in the Nevada Desert), taken part in ~40+ obstacle races and ex-Muay Thai fighter/coach so we will get you in shape to cross the finish line!

The plan:
Initially, weekly sessions on Saturday mornings at various locations around Stockholm. I will be there rain, hail or snow! #noexcuses We’ll organise an occasional social event too.

If anyone would like to help out in any way, that would be great! I can’t speak Svenska yet, so I’m particularly interested if anyone who can assist with translation etc. Instagram: Movelitefitness

Workouts:
The workouts will last approx. 1-1/4 hour and with an average. 50/50 split between running and exercise drills, although some will be more exercise focused and others more running focused. There will also be crawling (yes, on the grass/mud!), animal inspired movement and partner drills to keep things interesting and I guarantee you, no 2 workouts will be the same. Having done a lot of these races before, I’m very aware that just being able to run long distances is of limited benefit as you need a good level of strength to conquer the obstacles and therefore the workouts will have a high focus on full-body strength building. Post-workout fika may take place sometimes too!

Costs:
Free (we are a non-profit club) but I would kindly ask for an optional 20SEK/session voluntary donation to help cover the Meetup membership fees and most importantly, the rest will go to a ‘to be confirmed’ charity. The club in Edinburgh supported an animal sanctuary and I’d like to do the same here so we just need to decide which one we will support. Feel free to make any suggestions!

Training ethos:
Give it your best and train hard, but in a light-hearted, sociable manner and offer encouragement and support to your training partners. Feel free to invite your friends and importantly, positive vibes only on this group.

Hope to see you all soon for some kickass training! :-D
Carpe diem

Everyone is welcome to come and join us at Haga parkrun! Haga parkrun is a 5km timed run that takes place in Hagaparken every Saturday morning at 9.30, all year round. It's simple - sign up once at www.parkrun.se/register, print out your barcode and then just bring it along with you when you come to run! parkrun is the world's biggest running movement, with over 4 million registered worldwide, and over 200,000 people running each week at over 1200 events around the world. We also have events in Stockholm in Huddinge and Kungsängen.

category.name: fitness
description:
Hej obstacle racers! This group is for anyone (regardless of fitness level) interested in obstacle races/mud runs like Tough Viking, Toughest, Spartan Race etc., for anyone who enjoys exercising outside or wishes to get in shape to survive the pending zombie apocalypse. Let’s enjoy the great outdoors and put some training in for your upcoming events! I’ve created this group as I very recently moved to Stockholm and as I had a popular club in Edinburgh, I thought I would do the same here as it’s a good way to make friends, find people to become motivated with and do races alongside.

Please also join our new Facebook group:

https://www.facebook.com/groups/StockholmOCR/

Here are some of my credentials; top 10% contender in Worlds Toughest Mudder (24hour Obstacle Race in the Nevada Desert), taken part in ~40+ obstacle races and ex-Muay Thai fighter/coach so we will get you in shape to cross the finish line!

The plan:
Initially, weekly sessions on Saturday mornings at various locations around Stockholm. I will be there rain, hail or snow! #noexcuses We’ll organise an occasional social event too.

If anyone would like to help out in any way, that would be great! I can’t speak Svenska yet, so I’m particularly interested if anyone who can assist with translation etc. Instagram: Movelitefitness

Workouts:
The workouts will last approx. 1-1/4 hour and with an average. 50/50 split between running and exercise drills, although some will be more exercise focused and others more running focused. There will also be crawling (yes, on the grass/mud!), animal inspired movement and partner drills to keep things interesting and I guarantee you, no 2 workouts will be the same. Having done a lot of these races before, I’m very aware that just being able to run long distances is of limited benefit as you need a good level of strength to conquer the obstacles and therefore the workouts will have a high focus on full-body strength building. Post-workout fika may take place sometimes too!

Costs:
Free (we are a non-profit club) but I would kindly ask for an optional 20SEK/session voluntary donation to help cover the Meetup membership fees and most importantly, the rest will go to a ‘to be confirmed’ charity. The club in Edinburgh supported an animal sanctuary and I’d like to do the same here so we just need to decide which one we will support. Feel free to make any suggestions!

Training ethos:
Give it your best and train hard, but in a light-hearted, sociable manner and offer encouragement and support to your training partners. Feel free to invite your friends and importantly, positive vibes only on this group.

Hope to see you all soon for some kickass training! :-D
Carpe diem
name: Stockholm OCR & Fitness Club - Tough Viking Toughest etc

category.name: fitness
description:
Hej, välkomna till Promenera mera i Stockholm!<br>

Detta är en grupp för er som gillar att gå långpromenader i fantastiskt fina Stockholm året runt! Tanken bakom gruppen är att man ska kunna gå långpromenader med sällskap - för att det är trevligt och kul men också för att det är säkrare (speciellt under vinterhalvåret). Vi går oftast en gång i veckan, både innanför och utanför tullarna, och promenaderna brukar bli runt 8 till 10 km. Vi startar oftast någon gång mellan 18 och 19, och promenaderna tar ungefär 2 timmar. Tanken bakom den sena starttiden är att vi ska kunna hinna mötas upp efter arbetstidens slut, och eventuell hämtning av barn och/eller middag. Alla är välkomna, men det är bra om alla medlemmar orkar gå långa promenader i lagom rask takt. Det är inte powerwalk, men motionstakt. Barn i alla åldrar är välkomna, bara de klarar av att gå längre sträckor. På de flesta turer funkar det att ha barnvagn.

Alla medlemmar får organisera promenader, och alla medlemmar får komma med. Bjud gärna in vänner/bekanta/familj som gillar att promenera – ju fler desto roligare, men större grupp skapar också fler möjligheter att organisera promenader olika dagar i veckan på olika områden i Stockholm.

Promenera mera i Stockholm har gått ett 100-tal promenader sedan start i januari 2015, och många fler är planerade framöver! Vi har en Facebook-sida och en Meetup-grupp dit alla medlemmar är välkomna. Vi har även ett nyhetsbrev som hittills kommit ut två gånger. Förutom långpromenader har vi årligen: en barpromenad runt Södermalm, ca ett par kajakturer på sommaren, några kortare promenader anpassade för barn, och en fitness promenad där vi gör stopp vid utomhusgym. Vi är väldigt öppna för förslag!

Välkommen att promenera mera med oss!

Mail: promenera.mera.stockholm@gmail.com

Hemsida: http://promeneramerastockholm.weebly.com

Ni får gärna höra av er om förändringar eller idéer till våren, antingen här eller på vår mail promenera.mera.stockholm@gmail.com. Vi letar även efter medorganisatörer av varierad engagemangsnivå, så är ni intresserade eller vill veta mer, hör av er! <br>
name: Promenera mera i Stockholm
organizer.name: Linda
